  "brief": "<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Market Overview</h2>\n\nPre-market showing red across the board with SPY down 0.65% to $704.08 and VIX spiking 1.91% to 29.89. Iran war headlines dominating sentiment as geopolitical risk premium returns to markets. Small caps getting hit hardest with IWM down over 1%.\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> What to Watch</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Oil Inventory Data (2:30 PM):</strong> EIA crude stocks and Cushing data could be explosive given Middle East supply disruption fears</li>\n<li><strong>Mortgage Applications (11:00 AM):</strong> Full suite of MBA housing data as rates remain elevated</li>\n<li><strong>Energy Sector Momentum:</strong> XLE up 1.45% pre-market, only green sector as oil narrative builds</li>\n<li><strong>VIX Above 29:</strong> Fear gauge signaling potential volatility expansion if geopolitical tensions escalate</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-red\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚠ Bear Case</div>Iran conflict escalation crushes risk assets. Real estate and utilities getting demolished pre-market as rate fears combine with war premium. Broad sector weakness suggests institutional selling.</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Sector Rotation</h2>\n\nClassic risk-off rotation underway with energy the sole winner (+1.45%) as oil supply shock fears build. Real estate (-1.93%) and utilities (-1.75%) leading the carnage while tech showing surprising resilience at +0.08%. Flight to defensive plays getting crushed as duration risk meets geopolitical uncertainty.\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-amber\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚡ Key Driver</div>Iran war headlines driving everything. Multiple Reuters reports on Strait of Hormuz attacks, supply disruptions, and European energy crisis comparisons setting the narrative.</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-green\"><div class=\"callout-label\">✦ Bull Case</div>Tech holding up despite broad weakness suggests selective buying. Energy momentum could lift broader market if oil bulls take control. VIX spike could mark short-term capitulation bottom.</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Levels That Matter</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>SPY $700:</strong> Major psychological support, break triggers deeper selling</li>\n<li><strong>VIX $32:</strong> Next resistance level indicating serious fear escalation</li>\n<li><strong>XLE $95:</strong> Energy breakout level if oil narrative accelerates</li>\n<li><strong>QQQ $640:</strong> Tech support holding, loss opens $620 gap fill</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr>\n<p><em>Not a prediction. A preparation. Make your plan before the bell.</em></p>"
